What would have happened? Scholars over age 35 probably would have kept their jobs. I suspect that those under 35 would have fallen victim to lower staffing requirements if real wages had not been able to fall. Would nominal wages have started to fall if the inflation rate had been low? Perhaps, but not as easily as in an inflationary environment.
